Introduction

Digital literacy is an essential skill in today’s world. It helps students use technology effectively, communicate online, and stay safe on the internet. It also enables individuals to access information, create content, and interact responsibly in the digital environment. This presentation highlights the importance of digital literacy and how students can use digital tools effectively and safely.

----------------------------------------

What is Digital Literacy?

Digital literacy is the ability to use digital tools, technologies, and the internet effectively and safely. It includes skills such as searching for information, communicating through digital platforms, creating content, and understanding online safety.

----------------------------------------

Why is it Important?

• Helps in online learning and education  
• Improves communication and collaboration  
• Builds a strong professional identity  
• Increases productivity and efficiency  
• Protects users from cyber threats and scams  

----------------------------------------

Useful Digital Tools for Students

• GitHub  
A platform used to store, manage, and share coding projects.

• LinkedIn  
A professional networking platform used to connect with professionals and build career opportunities.

• Google Forms  
Used to create surveys, quizzes, and collect data easily.

• HackerRank  
A platform for practicing coding and improving problem-solving skills.

These tools help students enhance their skills and prepare for future career opportunities.

----------------------------------------

Safe Internet Practices

• Always use strong and unique passwords  
• Never share OTP, passwords, or personal information  
• Avoid clicking on unknown or suspicious links  
• Use trusted and secure websites  
• Keep your software and apps updated  

Following these practices helps protect your personal data and prevents cyber attacks.

----------------------------------------

Professional Online Presence

• Keep your profiles clean and professional  
• Use formal and respectful language  
• Share useful and relevant content  
• Avoid posting inappropriate or harmful content  

Maintaining a professional online presence helps in building a positive digital identity.

----------------------------------------

Conclusion

Digital literacy is a very important skill for students in the modern world. It helps in learning, communication, and career development. By using digital tools responsibly and following safe practices, students can build a secure and successful digital future.
